title.narrative: IMPROVED Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) SERVICES

description.narrative: Vulnerable girls and boys, adolescents and their families have increased access to water, sanitation, and hygiene services in targeted municipalities., which contributes to Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Social Protection, Social Protection (Covid), Water, Water (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 children, adolescents, youth and their families, especially the most disadvantaged, are increasingly using improved quality basic services.

sector.narrative: Sanitation - improving services in peri-urban and urban communities (except household water treatment and storage, moving up the ladder and strengthening sustainability)
Sanitation and hygiene - improving services in emergency communities
WASH - Enabling environment (policies/strategies, coordination, regulation, financing, planning-monitoring-review, sector capacity development and professionalization)
WASH in emergencies - institutions (schools, health care facilities, ECD centres) response including menstrual hygiene management
Water sector policy and administrative management
Water supply - safety/quality/treatment (including household treatment and safe storage)
Water supply and sanitation - large systems
Water supply in emergencies - improving water supply services communities
